{"word":"ὁδοποιέω","slug":"ὁδοποιέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὁδοποιέω</b></el> <el>(ὁδοποιέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ὁδοποίος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make</i> or <i>level a road</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, of roads, <i>to be made fit for use</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to reduce to a system</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to act as pioneer, serve as guide</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to make one's way, advance</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>progredi</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}